# Maintainer privacy (public repo)

This repository is public. **Do not write maintainer-private data into tracked files** unless the user explicitly accepts that exposure.

## Never commit or paste into user-facing prose

| Forbidden in README, release notes, website, `docs/`, `CLAUDE.md`, scripts | Use instead |
|---|---|
| Developer ID certificate **legal name** or full `spctl` / `codesign` `origin=` subject line | “Developer ID–signed and Apple-notarized”; verification expecting `source=Notarized Developer ID` only |
| Personal email, phone, physical address | “maintainer Apple ID email” or secrets/env only |
| `$HOME` paths (`/Users/<name>/...`) in docs | `PATH`, env var names, or “local maintainer tooling” |
| Device nicknames (`iPhone de …`) | Hardware model only (“paired iPhone 17 Pro”) |
| Hardware UDIDs, serial numbers in docs | Omit; cite run ids under `build/Debug/ios-device/runs/` |
| Hardcoded Apple **team ID** literals in scripts or docs | `APPLE_TEAM_ID`, `QWENVOICE_DEVELOPMENT_TEAM`, `QVOICE_IOS_TEAM_ID` — fail if unset, no repo default |
| Chat-only details the user shared for local debugging | Use in terminal only; do not propagate into commits |

## Allowed without scrubbing

- Apple **bundle IDs** (`com.patricedery.vocello`, engine extension, App Group) where signing/entitlements require them.
- Generic claims: “Developer ID”, “notarized”, “stapled ticket”.

## Before doc / README / website edits or commits

1. Read [`.cursor/rules/vocello-privacy.mdc`](vocello-privacy.mdc) (this file).
2. If you added or changed user-facing text, run a quick search for personal-name / team-id / UDID / home-path patterns under tracked paths (exclude `scratch/` unless committing it).
3. Prefer `scratch/` or private notes **outside git** for maintainer-only device notes.

## If the user asks to document signing trust

Explain notarization generically. Do **not** quote the certificate subject name from `spctl -vv` output into the README.
